text: Dellingr (Old Norse, possibly "the dayspring" or "shining one") is a god in the Norse mythology. He is a personification of a dawn. He married NÃ³tt (Night) and she bore him a son named Dagr (Day). The English family name Dallinger has been theorized as deriving from Dellingr. ==References== Category:Norse gods and goddesses
